# Tabletome iOS Agent Rules

**Start every session:** read [`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md) and [`docs/development/code-map.md`](../../docs/development/code-map.md).

## Documentation

| Need | Path |
|------|------|
| Doc hub | `docs/README.md` |
| Where is code? | `docs/development/code-map.md` |
| Setup / launch args | `docs/development/setup.md` |
| Add analytics event | `docs/development/playbooks/add-analytics-event.md` |
| Firebase / PII | `Support/Logging/AnalyticsMetadataKeys.swift` |
| Release gating | `Support/ReleaseSurface.swift` + `specs/ReleaseSurfaceSpec.md` |

## Architecture

- Domain (`Domain/`) must not import SwiftUI or UIKit.
- Features depend on repository protocols, never concrete JSON loaders.
- Data layer: use **callbacks** for analytics — do not import app logging types from Data targets.
- Gate unfinished features in `Support/ReleaseSurface.swift`.

## Git

- Do not commit `.xcodeproj`, `GoogleService-Info.plist`, or secrets.
- Do not push unless explicitly asked.
- Run `xcodegen generate` after `project.yml` changes.

## Accessibility

- Every interactive control: `accessibilityLabel`, `accessibilityHint`, `accessibilityIdentifier`.
- Minimum 44×44 pt touch targets.
- Use semantic Dynamic Type text styles.

## UI Tests

- Identifiers: `screen.element.action` (e.g. `home.gameSystem.aosSpearhead`).

## Specs

- Behavior changes require updating the matching spec Verification block.
- Brainstorm in `docs/brainstorm.md` is non-authoritative.
- Update `docs/feature-inventory.md` when scope changes.

## Layout

- Use `UIDevice.current.userInterfaceIdiom` for phone vs pad — not horizontal size class alone.

## Scope updates

When release stage or version changes, update `docs/release/status.md` and workspace project-status if applicable.
